casebody.data:
Kent, Respondent, v. Sibley, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 15, 1890.) Appeal from city court, general term. •

Argued before Larremore, 0. J., and Booicstaver and Bisohoff, JJ.

Le Barbier & Brewster, for appellant. Pelton & Poucher, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be affirmed, with costs. For former reports, see 5 N. Y. Supp. 448. See, also, Id. 447 ; 7 N. Y. Supp. 801.
